title: ICE: !ty.has_non_region_infer() -Cinstrument-coverage

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code Needs debug assertions ```Rust fn main() { use std::mem::{transmute, swap}; let a = 1; let b = 2; unsafe {swap::<&mut _>(transmute(&a), transmute(&b))}; //~^ ERROR type annotations needed } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.67.0-dev binary: rustc commit-hash: unknown commit-date: unknown host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.67.0-dev LLVM version: 15.0.4 ``` ### Error output `rustc ./issue-24013.rs -Cinstrument-coverage` ``` ```
